    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine sanctê et individuê Trinitatis. Tercius <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/237">Heinricus</persName> divina
                        favente clementia <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si circa sanctorum loca
                        beneficia condigna inpendimus, hoc nostram inperialem clêmentiam condecere
                        aestimamus, insuper etiam et êtêrna premia nos adipisci inde speramus.
                        Q[u]apropter omnium Christi nostrorumque fidelium universitatem scire
                        volumus, qualiter nos per interventum nostrae dilectae coniugis <persName
                            key="#Queen #Intercessory" ref="#people/365">AGNETIS</persName> et
                            <persName key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops #Intercessory"
                            ref="#people/2129">HERIMANNI</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/1850">Coloniensis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> nostri scilicet <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Chancellor #Intercessory" ref="#people/4324">Hunfredi</persName>
                        dilecti cancellarii caeterorumque familiarium nostrorum <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">abbaciaM</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Papal_concession #Rivers #Fisheries #Saltworks #Wine #Oil #Hay/fodder #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Exemption #Monasteries #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sanctae MARIE in <placeName
                                ref="#places/4179">Pomposia</placeName></orgName> de antecessore
                        nostro imperatore <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7"
                            >OTTONE</persName> a <persName key="#Archbishops" ref="#people/1568"
                            >Frederico</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1471"><placeName ref="#places/594"
                                >Ravennatis</placeName> Aecclesiae</orgName> archiepiscopo iuxta
                        utriusque placitum ad imperialem subiectionem concambitam ac postea ab
                            <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/130">HEINRICO</persName>
                        divae memoriae imperatore augusto nostro scilicet [a]ltero antecessore
                        corroboratam et ab <persName key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/3"
                            >Ugone</persName> marchione magnifice ditatam et in nos successione
                        imperii et legali iure hereditatam ad nostrae dominationis manus recepimus
                        eandemque cum omnibus pertinentiis suis et cum lateribus desuper in tota <rs
                            key="#Islands">insula</rs>, primo latere <placeName ref="#places/4657"
                            >Pado</placeName> percurrente in <rs key="#Sea">mare</rs>, secundo
                        latere <rs key="#Shores">litus maris</rs>, tercio latere <placeName
                            ref="#places/3563">Gauro</placeName>; insuper <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscaria</rs> quae vocatur <geogName key="#Fisheries"
                            ref="#estates/2457">Volana</geogName> a <rs key="#Rivers">rivo</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3575">Paderino</placeName> usque in
                            <rs key="#Sea">mare</rs> et locus qui dicitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/3559">Lacu Sancto</placeName> cum omnibus sibi
                        pertinentibus, quantacumque in apostolicae Sedis praecepto releguntur, vel
                        infra totum <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/485"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2449">Comacliensem</geogName></placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/80"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/84">Ferrariensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3538"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2435">Gavellensem</geogName></placeName> et in
                        civitate Ravenna et in comitatu <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3512"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2409"
                                >Corneliense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3513"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2458"
                                >Faventino</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3515"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2459"
                                >Liviense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/4602"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2480"
                                >Pupiliense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/1890"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1479"
                                >Cessenate</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/1806"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1480"
                                >Ariminense</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/1808"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2481"
                                >Fanense</geogName></placeName> et infra totum comitatum <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1812"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2371">Orbinatem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1803"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1481">Castellanum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/2752"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2462">Perusinum</geogName></placeName> , cum areis,
                        êdificiis, <rs key="#Castle">castris</rs>, <rs key="#Churches"
                        >capellis</rs>, <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder"
                            >[pr]atis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>, <rs>salictis</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Oil">olivetis</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montibus</rs>, <rs>planiciebus</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscationibus</rs>, <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >venationibus</rs>, <rs key="#Saltworks">salinis</rs> et cum omni
                        utilitate, quae vel nominari vel scribi possit, et quicquid sibi iunior UGO
                        marchio filius <persName><name ref="Hubertus">UBERTI</name></persName> dedit
                        et qua[ntacumque habet aut a]cquirere potest infra Padum et <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4646">Attesin</placeName> fluvium vel infra
                        Pa[dum et] <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3588">Sandalum</placeName>,
                            <rs key="#Exemption">ab omni subiectione archiepiscoporum
                        excutimus</rs>, ut regalis sit, nulli dominantium persone subiecta. Sin[t]
                        monachi eius ab omni secularis servicii infestatione securi, qui de suis
                        qualem voluerint aBBATEM eligant ab episcopo <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1498">Comacliensi</orgName> consecrandum; qui,
                        si sibi pro pecunia v[el] aliqua humana potestate molestus esse voluerit,
                        veniat ad arc[hi]episcopum Ravennatem ab eo benedicendus, et si hoc in isto
                        quod in priore invenerit, ad qualemcumque episcopum desiderat causa
                        consecrationis properet. Si quis autem hoc prêceptum fregerit, componat <rs
                            key="#Penalty">ducentas libras auri cocti</rs>, medietatem camere nostrê
                        et medietatem prêlibato monasterio. Quod ut verius credatur, hanc regalem
                        paginam MANU propria roboratam sigillari IUSSIMUS. Signum domni Heinrici
                        tercii (M) regis invictissimi . Hunfredus cancellarius vice Herimanni
                        archicancellarii recognovi . (SI D) Datum XVI kal. octub. ANNO incarnationis
                        Domini millesimo XLV, indictione XIIII, ANNO vero domni Heinrici tercii
                        regnantis septimo. Actum in <placeName ref="#places/4423"
                            >Potfelt</placeName>; feliciter AMEN.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>Mezzetti, <foreign>Le carte</foreign>, pp. 435-438, n° 195.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Enrico III conferma a Pomposa i diritti, le dipendenze, la libera elezione
                    dell'abate e prende il monastero sotto la sua tutela.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
